<P>
American Medical Merger Completed: A private investor group, which acquired 
American Medical International last October, said it completed a merger of the 
Beverly Hills-based hospital management concern with its holding company. AMI 
was purchased for $1.67 billion by the investor group jointly owned by First 
Boston Corp., current AMI Chairman Harry J. Gray and Mel Klein &amp; Partners. 
AMI became a wholly owned subsidiary of American Medical Holdings Inc. 
</P>
